				<h4 id="syntax">
					Syntax
				</h4>
				<p>
					The syntax for <mono>lua_setglobal</mono> calls is:
<div align="center" style="margin-top:-15px">
<mono>f++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline" style="margin-bottom:-15px">
lua_setglobal(string)
</pre>
</div><br>
<div align="center">
<mono>n++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline" style="margin-bottom:-15px">
\@lua_setglobal(string)
</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="description">
					Description
				</h4>
				<p>
					The <mono>lua_setglobal</mono> function takes a single string parameter, pops a value from the <mono>Lua</mono> stack and sets it as the value for a <mono>Lua</mono> global variable given the name of the input parameter, it is a binding for <a href="https://www.lua.org/manual/5.1/manual.html#lua_setglobal">this</a> function. 
				</p>

				<h4 id="f++-eg">
					f++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Example of <mono>lua_setglobal</mono> being used with <mono>f++</mono>:					

<div align="center" style="margin-top:-30px; margin-bottom:10px">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums">
lua_pushstring("hello, world!")
lua_setglobal("str")
lua
{
	print(str)
}</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="n++-eg">
					n++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Example of <mono>lua_setglobal</mono> being used with <mono>n++</mono>:					

<div align="center" style="margin-top:-30px; margin-bottom:10px">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums">
\@lua_pushstring("hello, world!")
\@lua_setglobal("str")
\@lua
{
	print(str)
}</pre>
</div>
				</p>
			</div>
